{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":662,"text":"I want to speak about \na forgotten conflict."},{"time":3474,"text":"It's a conflict that rarely\nhits the headlines."},{"time":7180,"text":"It happens right here,\nin the Democratic Republic of Congo."}]},{"cues":[{"time":12244,"text":"Now, most people outside of Africa\ndon't know much about the war in Congo,"},{"time":16842,"text":"so let me give you a couple of key facts."},{"time":20099,"text":"The Congolese conflict is the deadliest \nconflict since World War II."},{"time":25687,"text":"It has caused almost four million deaths."},{"time":28987,"text":"It has destabilized most of Central Africa\nfor the past 18 years."},{"time":33581,"text":"It is the largest ongoing\nhumanitarian crisis in the world."}]},{"cues":[{"time":38501,"text":"That's why I first went to Congo in 2001."},{"time":42162,"text":"I was a young humanitarian aid worker,\nand I met this woman who was my age."},{"time":47294,"text":"She was called Isabelle."},{"time":50868,"text":"Local militias\nhad attacked Isabelle's village."},{"time":54179,"text":"They had killed many men,\nraped many women."},{"time":57227,"text":"They had looted everything."},{"time":59224,"text":"And then they wanted to take Isabelle,"},{"time":61847,"text":"but her husband stepped in,"},{"time":63224,"text":"and he said, \"No,\nplease don't take Isabelle."},{"time":66422,"text":"Take me instead.\""},{"time":69709,"text":"So he had gone to the forest\nwith the militias,"},{"time":72700,"text":"and Isabelle had never seen him again."}]},{"cues":[{"time":76871,"text":"Well, it's because of people\nlike Isabelle and her husband"},{"time":80841,"text":"that I have devoted my career\nto studying this war"},{"time":83860,"text":"that we know so little about."}]},{"cues":[{"time":86638,"text":"Although there is one story\nabout Congo that you may have heard."},{"time":91262,"text":"It's a story about minerals and rape."},{"time":95214,"text":"Policy statements and media reports"},{"time":97800,"text":"both usually focus on a primary cause\nof violence in Congo --"},{"time":102534,"text":"the illegal exploitation and trafficking\nof natural resources --"},{"time":107312,"text":"and on a main consequence --"},{"time":110049,"text":"sexual abuse of women and girls\nas a weapon of war."}]},{"cues":[{"time":115243,"text":"So, not that these two issues\naren't important and tragic. They are."},{"time":122080,"text":"But today I want to tell you \na different story."},{"time":125978,"text":"I want to tell you a story\nthat emphasizes a core cause"},{"time":129596,"text":"of the ongoing conflict."},{"time":132283,"text":"Violence in Congo is in large part driven\nby local bottom-up conflicts"},{"time":139400,"text":"that international peace efforts\nhave failed to help address."}]},{"cues":[{"time":145325,"text":"The story starts from the fact\nthat not only is Congo notable"},{"time":150568,"text":"for being the world's worst\nongoing humanitarian crisis,"},{"time":154885,"text":"but it is also home to some of the largest"},{"time":158411,"text":"international peacebuilding\nefforts in the world."},{"time":162572,"text":"Congo hosts the largest"},{"time":164685,"text":"and most expensive United Nations\npeacekeeping mission in the world."},{"time":169530,"text":"It was also the site of the first\nEuropean-led peacekeeping mission,"},{"time":174229,"text":"and for its first cases ever,"},{"time":176903,"text":"the International Criminal Court\nchose to prosecute Congolese warlords."},{"time":183535,"text":"In 2006, when Congo held the first \nfree national elections in its history,"},{"time":190035,"text":"many observers thought that an end to \nviolence in the region had finally come."},{"time":196171,"text":"The international community lauded the \nsuccessful organization of these elections"},{"time":202300,"text":"as finally an example\nof successful international intervention"},{"time":206637,"text":"in a failed state."}]},{"cues":[{"time":209095,"text":"But the eastern provinces"},{"time":210853,"text":"have continued to face\nmassive population displacements"},{"time":214260,"text":"and horrific human rights violations."},{"time":217833,"text":"Shortly before I went\nback there last summer,"},{"time":220318,"text":"there was a horrible massacre\nin the province of South Kivu."},{"time":225217,"text":"Thirty-three people were killed."},{"time":227245,"text":"They were mostly women and children,"},{"time":229977,"text":"and many of them were hacked to death."},{"time":234116,"text":"During the past eight years,"},{"time":236069,"text":"fighting in the eastern provinces\nhas regularly reignited"},{"time":240007,"text":"full-scale civil and international war."},{"time":243074,"text":"So basically, every time we feel\nthat we are on the brink of peace,"},{"time":248055,"text":"the conflict explodes again."}]},{"cues":[{"time":250897,"text":"Why?"},{"time":252615,"text":"Why have the massive international efforts"},{"time":255587,"text":"failed to help Congo \nachieve lasting peace and security?"},{"time":262096,"text":"Well, my answer to this question\nrevolves around two central observations."},{"time":269064,"text":"First, one of the main reasons\nfor the continuation of violence in Congo"},{"time":275097,"text":"is fundamentally local --"},{"time":278005,"text":"and when I say local,"},{"time":279292,"text":"I really mean at the level\nof the individual, the family,"},{"time":282823,"text":"the clan, the municipality,\nthe community, the district,"},{"time":286712,"text":"sometimes the ethnic group."},{"time":289951,"text":"For instance, you remember the story\nof Isabelle that I told you."},{"time":294479,"text":"Well, the reason why militias\nhad attacked Isabelle's village"},{"time":298683,"text":"was because they wanted to take the land"},{"time":301793,"text":"that the villagers needed\nto cultivate food and to survive."}]},{"cues":[{"time":306508,"text":"The second central observation\nis that international peace efforts"},{"time":311278,"text":"have failed to help\naddress local conflicts"},{"time":315242,"text":"because of the presence\nof a dominant peacebuilding culture."},{"time":320161,"text":"So what I mean is that"},{"time":323777,"text":"Western and African diplomats,"},{"time":326150,"text":"United Nations peacekeepers, donors,"},{"time":328997,"text":"the staff of most\nnongovernmental organizations"},{"time":331601,"text":"that work with the resolution of conflict,"},{"time":334437,"text":"they all share a specific way\nof seeing the world."},{"time":339215,"text":"And I was one of these people,\nand I shared this culture,"},{"time":343221,"text":"so I know all too well how powerful it is."},{"time":347213,"text":"Throughout the world,\nand throughout conflict zones,"},{"time":351482,"text":"this common culture shapes\nthe intervener's understanding"},{"time":355290,"text":"of the causes of violence"},{"time":357774,"text":"as something that is primarily located\nin the national and international spheres."},{"time":364517,"text":"It shapes our understanding\nof the path toward peace"},{"time":367908,"text":"as something again that requires\ntop-down intervention"},{"time":371756,"text":"to address national\nand international tensions."},{"time":375879,"text":"And it shapes our understanding\nof the roles of foreign actors"},{"time":379598,"text":"as engaging in national\nand international peace processes."},{"time":385159,"text":"Even more importantly,\nthis common culture"},{"time":389034,"text":"enables international peacebuilders\nto ignore the micro-level tensions"},{"time":395234,"text":"that often jeopardize\nthe macro-level settlements."}]},{"cues":[{"time":400480,"text":"So for instance, in Congo,"},{"time":402581,"text":"because of how they are\nsocialized and trained,"},{"time":406795,"text":"United Nations officials,\ndonors, diplomats,"},{"time":409181,"text":"the staff of most\nnongovernmental organizations,"},{"time":412340,"text":"they interpret continued fighting\nand massacres as a top-down problem."},{"time":419350,"text":"To them, the violence they see"},{"time":421574,"text":"is the consequence of tensions\nbetween President Kabila"},{"time":426554,"text":"and various national opponents,"},{"time":429224,"text":"and tensions between Congo,\nRwanda and Uganda."},{"time":434217,"text":"In addition, these international \npeacebuilders view local conflicts"},{"time":440288,"text":"as simply the result\nof national and international tensions,"},{"time":446081,"text":"insufficient state authority,"},{"time":448496,"text":"and what they call the Congolese people's\nso-called inherent penchant for violence."}]},{"cues":[{"time":455364,"text":"The dominant culture\nalso constructs intervention"},{"time":459316,"text":"at the national and international levels"},{"time":462149,"text":"as the only natural and legitimate task\nfor United Nations staffers and diplomats."},{"time":469362,"text":"And it elevates the organization\nof general elections,"},{"time":473721,"text":"which is now a sort of cure-all,"},{"time":475807,"text":"as the most crucial state\nreconstruction mechanism"},{"time":479591,"text":"over more effective\nstate-building approaches."},{"time":483116,"text":"And that happens not only in Congo\nbut also in many other conflict zones."}]},{"cues":[{"time":489343,"text":"But let's dig deeper,"},{"time":491243,"text":"into the other main sources of violence."},{"time":495193,"text":"In Congo, continuing violence"},{"time":497862,"text":"is motivated not only by the national\nand international causes"},{"time":502875,"text":"but also by longstanding\nbottom-up agendas"},{"time":507182,"text":"whose main instigators\nare villagers, traditional chiefs,"},{"time":511143,"text":"community chiefs or ethnic leaders."},{"time":514141,"text":"Many conflicts revolve around political,\nsocial and economic stakes"},{"time":520116,"text":"that are distinctively local."},{"time":522944,"text":"For instance, there is\na lot of competition"},{"time":525920,"text":"at the village or district level"},{"time":528308,"text":"over who can be chief of village\nor chief of territory"},{"time":531894,"text":"according to traditional law,"},{"time":534468,"text":"and who can control\nthe distribution of land"},{"time":537696,"text":"and the exploitation\nof local mining sites."},{"time":541215,"text":"This competition often results\nin localized fighting,"},{"time":545436,"text":"for instance in one village or territory,"},{"time":549220,"text":"and quite frequently,\nit escalates into generalized fighting,"},{"time":553163,"text":"so across a whole province,"},{"time":555292,"text":"and even at times\ninto neighboring countries."}]},{"cues":[{"time":558631,"text":"Take the conflict between Congolese \nof Rwandan descent"},{"time":563698,"text":"and the so-called indigenous \ncommunities of the Kivus."},{"time":568609,"text":"This conflict started in the 1930s\nduring Belgian colonization,"},{"time":573995,"text":"when both communities competed\nover access to land and to local power."},{"time":579328,"text":"Then, in 1960,\nafter Congolese independence,"},{"time":582727,"text":"it escalated because each camp\ntried to align with national politicians,"},{"time":588578,"text":"but still to advance their local agendas."},{"time":592512,"text":"And then, at the time\nof the 1994 genocide in Rwanda,"},{"time":596880,"text":"these local actors allied\nwith Congolese and Rwandan armed groups,"},{"time":603059,"text":"but still to advance their local agendas\nin the provinces of the Kivus."},{"time":608389,"text":"And since then, these local disputes\nover land and local power"},{"time":614023,"text":"have fueled violence,"},{"time":615743,"text":"and they have regularly jeopardized"},{"time":617989,"text":"the national and\ninternational settlements."}]},{"cues":[{"time":623542,"text":"So we can wonder why\nin these circumstances"},{"time":627347,"text":"the international peacebuilders\nhave failed to help implement"},{"time":632029,"text":"local peacebuilding programs."},{"time":635407,"text":"And the answer is that\ninternational interveners"},{"time":640253,"text":"deem the resolution of grassroots conflict"},{"time":643776,"text":"an unimportant, unfamiliar,\nand illegitimate task."},{"time":650410,"text":"The very idea of becoming involved\nat the local level clashes fundamentally"},{"time":656389,"text":"with existing cultural norms,"},{"time":658497,"text":"and it threatens\nkey organizational interests."},{"time":662380,"text":"For instance, the very identity\nof the United Nations"},{"time":666997,"text":"as this macro-level\ndiplomatic organization"},{"time":670353,"text":"would be upended\nif it were to refocus on local conflicts."},{"time":676761,"text":"And the result is that\nneither the internal resistance"},{"time":681486,"text":"to the dominant ways of working"},{"time":683833,"text":"nor the external shocks"},{"time":686576,"text":"have managed to convince international\nactors that they should reevaluate"},{"time":691018,"text":"their understanding\nof violence and intervention."},{"time":695560,"text":"And so far, there have been\nonly very few exceptions."},{"time":699333,"text":"There have been exceptions,\nbut only very few exceptions,"},{"time":702796,"text":"to this broad pattern."}]},{"cues":[{"time":706214,"text":"So to wrap up,\nthe story I just told you"},{"time":709526,"text":"is a story about how\na dominant peacebuilding culture"},{"time":714475,"text":"shapes the intervener's understanding\nof what the causes of violence are,"},{"time":719282,"text":"how peace is made,"},{"time":720963,"text":"and what interventions should accomplish."},{"time":724575,"text":"These understandings enable\ninternational peacebuilders"},{"time":728324,"text":"to ignore the micro-level foundations"},{"time":731402,"text":"that are so necessary\nfor sustainable peace."},{"time":736051,"text":"The resulting inattention\nto local conflicts"},{"time":739044,"text":"leads to inadequate peacebuilding\nin the short term"},{"time":743062,"text":"and potential war resumption\nin the long term."},{"time":747068,"text":"And what's fascinating\nis that this analysis"},{"time":750214,"text":"helps us to better understand\nmany cases of lasting conflict"},{"time":754224,"text":"and international intervention failures,\nin Africa and elsewhere."},{"time":759513,"text":"Local conflicts fuel violence\nin most war and post-war environments,"},{"time":765074,"text":"from Afghanistan to Sudan\nto Timor-Leste,"},{"time":768765,"text":"and in the rare cases\nwhere there have been comprehensive,"},{"time":772366,"text":"bottom-up peacebuilding initiatives,"},{"time":775453,"text":"these attempts have been successful\nat making peace sustainable."},{"time":780947,"text":"One of the best examples is the contrast"},{"time":783757,"text":"between the relatively peaceful\nsituation in Somaliland,"},{"time":788168,"text":"which benefited from sustained\ngrassroots peacebuilding initiatives,"},{"time":793378,"text":"and the violence prevalent\nin the rest of Somalia,"},{"time":797586,"text":"where peacebuilding\nhas been mostly top-down."},{"time":800945,"text":"And there are several other cases"},{"time":803246,"text":"in which local, grassroots\nconflict resolution"},{"time":806961,"text":"has made a crucial difference."}]},{"cues":[{"time":809980,"text":"So if we want international\npeacebuilding to work,"},{"time":814052,"text":"in addition to any top-down intervention,"},{"time":817874,"text":"conflicts must be resolved\nfrom the bottom up."},{"time":821545,"text":"And again, it's not that national\nand international tensions don't matter."},{"time":826197,"text":"They do."},{"time":827923,"text":"And it's not that national\nand international peacebuilding"},{"time":831155,"text":"isn't necessary."},{"time":832617,"text":"It is."},{"time":834000,"text":"Instead, it is that both macro-level\nand micro-level peacebuilding are needed"},{"time":841255,"text":"to make peace sustainable,"},{"time":843972,"text":"and local nongovernmental organizations,"},{"time":846113,"text":"local authorities and \ncivil society representatives"},{"time":849092,"text":"should be the main actors\nin the bottom-up process."}]},{"cues":[{"time":853702,"text":"So of course, there are obstacles."},{"time":856131,"text":"Local actors often lack the funding"},{"time":858786,"text":"and sometimes the logistical means\nand the technical capacity"},{"time":862323,"text":"to implement effective,\nlocal peacebuilding programs."},{"time":866857,"text":"So international actors\nshould expand their funding and support"},{"time":871913,"text":"for local conflict resolution."}]},{"cues":[{"time":875700,"text":"As for Congo, what can be done?"},{"time":879056,"text":"After two decades of conflict\nand the deaths of millions,"},{"time":882780,"text":"it's clear that we need\nto change our approach."},{"time":886545,"text":"Based on my field research,"},{"time":888223,"text":"I believe that international\nand Congolese actors"},{"time":891733,"text":"should pay more attention\nto the resolution of land conflict"},{"time":895159,"text":"and the promotion\nof inter-community reconciliation."},{"time":899679,"text":"So for instance,\nin the province of the Kivus,"},{"time":902321,"text":"the Life and Peace Institute\nand its Congolese partners"},{"time":905589,"text":"have set up inter-community forums"},{"time":908684,"text":"to discuss the specifics\nof local conflicts over land,"},{"time":913036,"text":"and these forums have found solutions\nto help manage the violence."},{"time":918671,"text":"That's the kind of program\nthat is sorely needed"},{"time":922290,"text":"throughout eastern Congo."},{"time":925097,"text":"It's with programs like this"},{"time":926975,"text":"that we can help people\nlike Isabelle and her husband."}]},{"cues":[{"time":931925,"text":"So these will not be magic wands,"},{"time":934448,"text":"but because they take into account\ndeeply rooted causes of the violence,"},{"time":940116,"text":"they could definitely be game-changers."}]},{"cues":[{"time":942950,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":945504,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}